FBIS3-31268 "dreeu032_d_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-032 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Feb 1994 SLOVAKIA Roman Kovac Expelled From Ruling Party LD1502154094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1500 GMT 15 Feb 94 LD1502154094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Language: Czech Article Type:BFN [Text] Slovak Deputy Prime Minister Roman Kovac and Foreign Minister Jozef Moravcik have been expelled from the ruling party Movement for a Democratic Slovakia. The Movement's press spokewoman Ivana Salczerova confirmed this today. The two politicians called last week for forming a new government as a broader coalition with the opposition, but without chairmen of political parties, including Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar.
